His Grace was most zealous and indefatigable in his efforts for the salvation of souls. The means he adopted to obtain that end were truly apostolic. In his visitations of the islands under his jurisdicti0n‚ he usually took with him three or four priests skilled in giving missions, and he held in the parishes visited by him, a Novana.
